After being prompted several times by Rigamonti, Leo adds that during a recent court appearance his mother 'threatened me to say tons of bad things about my dad.'

Authorities began a Europe-wide search for the father and his son two 
weeks ago after the boy's mother, Laura Carder went to collect her son but found the pair 
missing, according to La Repubblica.

On January 9 the boy's grandfather claimed the pair had gone to Trentino, in northern Italy, for a skiing holiday, though Carder believes Rigamonti may have fled to Spain.

Carder, an American, has previously claimed the boy suffered years of domestic abuse at the hands of his father and has since had to undergo therapy.

